The paper deals with optimization of power allocation and load balancing in a distributed antenna system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of Cell-free Massive MIMO technology also involves system-level optimization (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes low-complexity algorithms, which can be considered as a machine learning approach (cs.LG).
